2 unit(s) Beyond Meat®
2 tbsp Tomato Sauce Base
6 unit(s) Flour Tortillas
¾ cup Mozzarella Cheese, shredded
7 g Cilantro
1 unit(s) Lime
170 g Coleslaw Cabbage Mix
4 tbsp Mayonnaise
1 unit(s) Jalapeño
2 tbsp Mexican Seasoning
2 unit(s) Green Onion
1 tsp Sugar*
½ tbsp Oil*
0.13 tsp Pepper*
0.13 tsp Salt*

Zest lime, then juice half. Cut remaining lime into wedges.
Thinly slice green onions.
Roughly chop cilantro.
Core, then finely chop jalapeño, removing seeds for less heat. (TIP: We suggest using gloves when prepping jalapeños!)

Heat a large non-stick pan over medium-high heat.
When hot, add 1/2 tbsp (1 tbsp) oil, then Beyond Meat® patties and jalapeños. Cook, breaking up patties into smaller pieces, until crispy, 5-6 min.**
Add half the Mexican Seasoning, then stir to coat Beyond Meat® and jalapeños.

Add tomato sauce base and 1/3 cup (2/3 cup) water to the pan with Beyond Meat® and jalapeños.
Bring to a boil, then reduce heat to medium. Season with salt and pepper. Cook, stirring often, until sauce thickens, 3-4 min.

Meanwhile, whisk together mayo, lime juice, lime zest, remaining Mexican Seasoning and 1 tsp (2 tsp) sugar in a large bowl.
Add coleslaw cabbage mix and half the green onions. Season with salt and pepper, then toss to combine.

Arrange tortillas on a parchment-lined baking sheet. (NOTE: For 4 ppl, use 2 baking sheets.)
Divide Beyond Meat® filling between tortillas.
Sprinkle cheese over top.
Bake tacos in the middle of the oven until cheese melts, 3-4 min. (NOTE: For 4 ppl, bake in the middle and top of the oven.)

Divide tacos between plates. Serve creamy slaw alongside.
Sprinkle cilantro and remaining green onions over tacos.
Squeeze a lime wedge over top, if desired.

If you've opted to get Beyond Meat®, cook it the same way as the chorizo, breaking up patties into smaller pieces, until crispy, 5-6 min.** Disregard instructions to drain excess fat.